-- Ukraine May Resume VAT Payment to Grain Exporters, Izvestia Says
-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 2012-03-07T07:16:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/ukraine-may-resume-vat-payment-to-grain-exporters-izvestia-says.html
Ukraine will push the Cabinet to
restore payment of a value-added tax to grain exporters to spur
cereal shipments,  Ekonomicheskie Izvestia  newspaper reported,
citing Agriculture Minister Mykola Prysyazhnyuk.  Ukraine exported 12.7 million metric tons of grains as
of March 6 since the beginning of the marketing year of July 1,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
